    "The following year, in a dramatic switch of field emphasis, Focillon succeeded <a href=\"/malee\">\u00c9mile M\u00e2le</a> in 1924 as the chair of medieval archaeology at the Sorbonne, a fact Focillon attributed to his having taught in cities with great medieval churches as much as a<em>New York Times</em>hing else.": [
